  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

        FN patients expected to have at least 5 days or more of neutropenia will be eligible for
        treatment with garlic compounds AST/ALT ≤ 3 times the upper limit of institutional
        laboratory normal.

        Total bilirubin ≤ 2 times the upper limit of institutional laboratory normal.

        BUN and creatinine should be ≤ 3 times the upper limit of institutional laboratory normal.

        Newly diagnosed as well as previously treated patients will be eligible.

        Exclusion Criteria:

        History of clinically significant liver or kidney disease.

        Patients on anti-coagulation therapy with Coumadin will be excluded because of the
        potential garlic interference with metabolism.

        Patients receiving concomitant chemotherapeutic treatment
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
